om the Original Motion Picture \"Ralph Breaks The Internet\") |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j60ClcNYWu4 |website=www.youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=23 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Bad Liar\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| Ryan Reichenfeld<ref>{{cite web |title=Imagine Dragons - Bad Liar |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I-QfPUz1es8 |website=www.youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Birds\"\n| Zac Wong<ref>{{cite web |title=Imagine Dragons - Birds (Animated Video) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vOXZkm9p_zY |website=www.youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=24 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Nothing Left to Say\"\n| 2020\n|\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.imaginedragonsmusic.com/ Official website]\n* [http://www.allmusic.com/artist/imagine-dragons-mn0002040645 Imagine Dragons] at [[AllMusic]]\n* {{Discogs artist |artist=Imagine Dragons |name=Imagine Dragons}}\n* {{MusicBrainz artist |id=012151a8-0f9a-44c9-997f-ebd68b5389f9 |name=Imagine Dragons}}\n\n{{Imagine Dragons}}\n\n[[Category:Discographies of American artists]]\n[[Category:Rock music group discographies]]\n[[Category:Imagine Dragons|Discography]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist          = [[Imagine Dragons]]\n| Image           = Imagine Dragons, 2012.jpg\n| Caption         = Imagine Dragons on the set of their performance on [[Walmart|Walmart Soundcheck]]\n| Alt             = Four Caucasian men wearing jackets stand in front of a wall bearing a car mural.\n| Studio          = 4\n| Live            = 4\n| EP              = 10\n| Singles         = 25\n| Music videos    = 19\n| Option          = 6\n| Option name     = Promotional singles\n}}\n\nThe American [[pop rock]] band [[Imagine Dragons]] has released four [[studio album]]s, four [[live album]]s, ten [[extended play]]s, twenty-five [[Single (music)|single]]s, six [[promotional single]]s and nineteen [[music video]]s. The band released their debut extended play, \"Speak to Me\" in 2008. \n[[Imagine Dragons (EP)|The self-titled debut extended play]], ''[[Hell and Silence]]'' and ''[[It's Time (EP)|It's Time]]'' followed in September 2009, June 2010, and March 2011 respectively. Imagine Dragons later found commercial success with the release of their fifth extended play, ''[[Continued Silence]]'', in February 2012. \"[[It's Time (Imagine Dragons song)|It's Time]]\" was released as the lead single from the EP, peaking at number fifteen on the United States [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref name=\"US-singles\"/> It has since sold over 3 million copies in the United States. ''Continued Silence'' went on to peak at number 40 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] in the United States.<ref name=\"US-albums\"/>\n\n''[[Night Visions]]'', the band's debut studio album, was released in September 2012; it peaked at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200 and topped the ''Billboard'' [[Billboard charts|Top Alternative Albums]] and ''Billboard'' [[Billboard charts|Top Rock Albums]] charts.<ref name=\"US-albums\"/><ref name=\"US-Alternative-albums\"/> In addition to \"It's Time\", the album also contains the singles \"[[Radioactive (Imagine Dragons song)|Radioactive]]\" and \"[[Demons (Imagine Dragons song)|Demons]]\". The former single peaked at number three on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 and has since sold over 8.6 million copies in the United States.<ref name=\"RUSSales\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/6620412/imagine-dragons-radioactive-riaa-certified-diamond |title=Imagine Dragons' 'Radioactive' is now RIAA Certified Diamond |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=July 8, 2015 |accessdate=August 6, 2015}}</ref> It also became a top\u2013ten hit in numerous countries, such as Australia, Germany and Sweden.<ref name=\"AUS\"/><ref name=\"GER\"/><ref name=\"SWE\">{{cite web |url=http://swedishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Imagine+Dragons |title=Discography Imagine Dragons |work=swedishcharts.com |publisher=Hung Medien |accessdate=January 18, 2013}}</ref> \"Demons\" has since sold 5 million copies in the US and peaked at number six on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref name=\"US-singles\"/><ref name=\"USSales\">{{cite web|url=https://music.yahoo.com/photos/top-selling-rock-songs-slideshow/ |title=The 15 Most Downloaded Songs in Rock History |author=Christopher Polk |publisher=[[Yahoo! Music]] |date=January 31, 2015 |accessdate=August 6, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150204045408/https://music.yahoo.com/photos/top-selling-rock-songs-slideshow/ |archivedate=February 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe band's second studio album, ''[[Smoke + Mirrors]]'', was released in February 2015, debuting at the top of the ''Billboard'' 200.  The band followed this with their third studio album, ''[[Evolve (Imagine Dragons album)|Evolve]]'', in June 2017.  The record was preceded by two singles, \"[[Believer (Imagine Dragons song)|Believer]]\" and [[Thunder (Imagine Dragons song)|Thunder]]\", which both went on to peak at number four on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.  They were then followed by a third single, \"[[Whatever It Takes (Imagine Dragons song)|Whatever It Takes]]\", which reached number 12.  All three songs have peaked at number one on the [[Hot Rock Songs]] chart. After the Evolve tour was completed, they released their fourth studio album ''[[Origins (Imagine Dragons album)|Origins]]'' on November 9, 2018. Five singles have been released from the album: \"[[Natural (Imagine Dragons song)|Natural]]\", \"[[Zero (Imagine Dragons song)|Zero]]\", \"[[Machine (Imagine Dragons song)|Machine]]\", \"[[Bad Liar (Imagine Dragons song)|Bad Liar]]\", and \"Birds\" featuring [[Elisa (Italian singer)|Elisa]].\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of stu