Scotia Yacht Squadron]]\n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = 28 February 2020\n}}\n\n'''Philip Gow''' (born 26 January 1962) is a Canadian sailor from [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]]. who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Busan]], [[South Korea]] as crew member in the [[Soling]]. With helmsman [[Paul Thomson (sailor)|Paul Thomson]] and fellow crew members [[Stuart Flinn]] they took the 12th place.<ref name=\"OS1988\" /> The same team competed in the [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]] were they took the 7th place.<ref name=\"OS1992\" />\n{{Footer Canadian Championship Winners in Soling}}\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n  <ref name = Sports-Reference>{{cite web\n                                  |url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20121107112119/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fl/stuart-flinn-1.html\n                                  |title      = Philip Gow Bio, Stats, and Results \n                                  |publisher  = Sports-Reference.com \n                                  |work       = Olympic Sports \n                                  |accessdate = 28 February 2020 \n                                  |url-status = live\n                                  |df=dmy \n                                }}</ref>\n  <ref name = OS1988>{{cite web\n                        | url        = https://digital.la84.org/digital/collection/p17103coll8/id/32564/rec/53\n                        | title      = Official Report : Games of the XXIVth Olympiad, Seoul 1988, v.2\n                        | year       = 1988\n                        | format     = PDF\n                        | accessdate = 27 February 2020\n                       }}</ref>\n  <ref name = OS1992>{{cite web\n                        | url        = https://digital.la84.org/digita